# Example .gitignore for a single-repository workflow.
#
# In a real project, this file would usually be named .gitignore.
# The goal is to keep both real data and generated stand-in data out of Git,
# while keeping the folder skeleton and reusable code tracked.

# Operating system and editor files
.DS_Store
.Rhistory
.RData
.Ruserdata/
.Rproj.user/
.quarto/
*_cache/
*_files/
*.knit.md
*.utf8.md

# Real data must not be committed.
real-data/data/*
!real-data/data/.gitkeep

# Outputs extracted from real data require review before sharing.
real-data/outputs/*
!real-data/outputs/.gitkeep

# Approved metadata copied for simulation may still be project-sensitive.
sim-data/metadata/*
!sim-data/metadata/.gitkeep

# Generated simulated data are development artifacts, not source files.
sim-data/data/*
!sim-data/data/.gitkeep

# Local secrets or credentials
.env
.Renviron
